Introduction

ShareSimple provides a simple way to share sensitive data over email with end-to-end encryption, consent management, One Time Passwords and full auditlog.

This is the documentation for the ShareSimple v1.0.3 API. Read the contents of this page carefully, including the Restrictions and Responsibilities, to understand how to use ShareSimple APIs.

 

1.    API References

This is the reference for the ShareSimple REST APIs. This APIs are the primary way to interact with ShareSimple remotely for any integration. This page documents the REST resources available in ShareSimple, along with expected HTTP response codes and sample requests.

Note that while all endpoints from the v1.0.3 API are available, they are currently under development. This means that any endpoint can change at any time.

 

2.    Authentication

Authentication to the API is performed via HTTP Basic Auth. The ShareSimple API uses userid and token parameters in the Request Header for simple, but effective authentication and authorization. The one thing to keep in mind is that all requests to the API must be made over SSL (https:// not http://).

 

Is authentication needed?

ShareSimple APIs require authentication parameters, specifically requests from different user groups. Authenticated requests require userid and token as Request Header parameters. These tokens are unique to a user and should be stored securely.

 

3.    Common use cases

The ShareSimple APIs perform a variety of tasks, supporting both company and user accounts.

         Manage company data and preferences.

         Manage user creation, update and status change.

         Folder creation, file upload and delete, etc.

 

Getting Started

 

Based on simple REST principles, the ShareSimple Web API endpoints return JSON data about company, customers, file management, send or request data, etc. from the ShareSimple application. Unless otherwise specified, all of ShareSimple's APIs will return the information that you request in the JSON data format.

1.    Base address

The base address of Web API is

 

https://sharesimple.azurewebsites.net/api

 

The API provides a set of endpoints, each with its own unique path. To access private data through the Web API, such as user profiles, activity and file uploads.

 

2.    Requests

The ShareSimple API is a RESTful API that accesses data resources via standard HTTPS requests in UTF-8 format to an API endpoint. And the Web API uses a simple JSON input and output format for each action. You must supply a Content-Type: application/json header in PUT and POST requests.

 

Method

Action

 

GET

Retrieves resources

 

POST

Creates resources

 

PUT

Changes and/or replaces resources or collections

 

DELETE

Deletes resources

 

 

3.    Authentication Parameters

The following parameters need to be used in the API Request Headers for accessing private/authenticated data.

Parameters

Description

Default Value

userid

The unique string identifying the ShareSimple user that you can find at the end of the URI for the user.

 

token

Access tokens allow ShareSimple to identify the user access to ShareSimple and the permission to access requested data.

 

 

4.    Responses

The ShareSimple Web API returns all response data as a JSON object. The APIs respond to successful requests with HTTP status codes in the 200 or 300 range and error status with rage 500. When you create or update a resource, the API renders the resulting JSON representation in the response body.

 

Users

Using the following request user information can be viewed, modified and can also be created.

1.    HTTP requests

ShareSimple user data can be retrieved, modified and new users can be created using the following HTTP request with the API.

Actions

Protocol

URI

Description

URIs relative to base url https://sharesimple.azurewebsites.net/api, if not specified otherwise.

Request a single user

GET

/user/{id}

Requests the user with the requested user id to be retrieved from the server.

Request all users from a specific company

GET

/user/company/{id}

Requests all users under the Company with the requested company id to be retrieved from the server.

Request user creation

POST

/user

Requests a user to be created with the provided array of data. (payload parameters specified in later section)

Request a user modification

PUT

/user/{id}

Requests the user with the requested user id to be modified in the server. (payload parameters specified in later section)
